we're not going to succeed.

00:00:46.361 --> 00:00:48.110
And so as somebody who
works on coral reef

00:00:48.110 --> 00:00:51.290
conservation on a daily basis
and thinks about these systems,

00:00:51.290 --> 00:00:52.970
we're really trying
to figure out,

00:00:52.970 --> 00:00:56.910
what are reasonable answers
to this big question?

00:00:56.910 --> 00:00:58.910
And I don't know,
has anyone here heard

00:00:58.910 --> 00:01:00.557
about coral reefs in
the news recently?

00:01:00.557 --> 00:01:01.640
Can I see a show of hands?

00:01:01.640 --> 00:01:05.450
Heard anything about--
so pretty much everybody.

00:01:05.450 --> 00:01:07.561
Probably had to do with
